fields.description:
I deleted a repository, and then created another with the same name. I am no longer able to clone this repository. It is not private, and I am just copying the URL given on the repository page. This is what I get:

{{git clone https://garfieldnate@bitbucket.org/garfieldnate/perl-xml-libxml_ns-uniquekey-fork}} yields:

{code}
fatal: https://garfieldnate@bitbucket.org/garfieldnate/perl-xml-libxml_ns-uniquekey-fork/info/refs?service=git-upload-pack not found: did you run git update-server-info on the server?
{code}

I have waited a couple of weeks and nothing has changed. Any tips on how to fix this?

If I add a comment on a changeset with this text:

{code}
[External link][1].

[1]: http://example.net/#comment:1
{code}

Then I see a link back to the _current commit_ instead of the external site I really wanted to link to. I&#x27;ve left a demo here: https://bitbucket.org/mg/bitbucket-test/commits/5c13c6683ff0 (notice how nice a short link it, I wish I could just copy that directly from my address bar...).

{code}
#!

Uncaught TypeError: Cannot call method &#x27;remove&#x27; of undefined form-dialog.js:283
{code}

when click on the cross to delete a group under Manage Account >> Groups

*Browsers tested:*

Chrome Versie 29.0.1547.65

Safari Versie 6.0.5 (7536.30.1)

OSX 10.7.5

Something like on Jira

{code}
[X] undone task
[/] done task
{code}

or on [GitHub|https://help.github.com/articles/github-flavored-markdown#task-lists]

{code}
- [ ] undone task
- [x] done task
{code}
